Cats are obligate carnivores, meaning they require a diet of meat to survive. They can be fed commercial cat food, which is specially formulated to meet their nutritional needs, or they can be fed a diet of raw or cooked meats.

Cats are obligate carnivores, meaning they require a diet of primarily meat in order to survive. Common foods that cats eat include wet and dry cat food, raw meat, cooked eggs, and small amounts of dairy products.
